{
  "texts": [
    "Recently, a new dataset called Commonsense Validation and Explanation (ComVE) [11] has been proposed; instead of merely selecting an answer from a set of choices, the machine is required to generate coherent explanations that demonstrate a deeper understanding of the underlying commonsense principles in ComVE.",
    "In this paper, we focus on the challenging task of explanation generation for commonsense reasoning.",
    "The objective of the commonsense explanation generation task is to generate a sentence that explains why a given nonsensical statement contradicts commonsense knowledge, which is shown in Fig. 1.",
    "Existing approaches to this task typically fall into two categories: sequence-to-sequence (seq2seq) and generative methods.",
    "The seq2seq models [12][13][14] take a nonsensical statement as input and use an encoder-decoder architecture to generate explanatory sentences."
  ]
}